<p>Employee engagement is crucial; not just for its own sake, but because it is directly connected to business outcomes. Companies with engagement levels in the top 25 percent experience nearly double the rates of success across a wide-ranging set of metrics including “financial, customer, retention, safety, quality, shrinkage and absenteeism.” Employee engagement brings numerous benefits &#8212; it can [&#8230;]</p>
